      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GIPSY PRINCESS (5) has been tackling stronger company at Menangle of late and while down the track last time she had produced a series of decent efforts prior when not too far off the placings. Owns a strong record at this circuit and distance so looks well placed. DOUBLE IT HARRY (8) backs up off a good effort to place at Menangle last Saturday. Has been going very well winning four of his previous five starts, three of them here including a 5.8m success from this barrier two back. ALTA SIERRA (4) hasn't raced for five months but strikes at 50 per cent when fresh and has been readied by placing in two trials. AMERICAN HAMMER NZ (1) raced parked and stuck on for second the last time he raced here last month and should enjoy a soft run from the ace draw.",
